review_blob: Heavy fruity flavor. It makes a good first impression. really does not taste like a Scottish Ale. There is a sweet banana thing going on.  The taste seems artificially sweet. I am enjoying this but it is overly fruity.

Listen, I understand why beer snobs dont show more love for this beer as it is not all that amazing but finer craft beers usually are not "ballgame" beers that is you cant toss back a six pack during a game because they are just too rich.  This is a ballgame beer that tastes great.  I can drink several and not feel like I just ate a pound of chocolate.
I like it. weak head. great alcohol finish. other great flavors I am not great at describing but I do like this one.
beer_name: Left Hand Wake Up Dead Imperial Stout - Barrel-Aged
